Introduction

As we know,In recent years Turkish lira depreciated against dollar and euro.I downloaded some data that this loss of value might affect from EVDS.One of them is Cumhuriyet Gold Selling Price, because their price indexed to dollar.Also, I think Consumer Price Index is affected because Turkey imports esential goods and If dollar and euro increase, their price also increase.ALso, total credit given by banks may be affected by fluctuation in exchange rates because borrowing with dollar or euro is quite common.Also, Import and Export may be affected by fluctuation in exchange rates because euro or dollar is used in trade.

Date<-xts(data, order.by = as.Date(as.yearmon(data$Date)))
Date <- subset( Date, select = -Date )
Date<-data.table(Date)
data <- subset( data, select = -Date )
USD<-data$USD  
ts.USD<-ts(data =USD, start = 2007, end = 2019, frequency = 12,  deltat = 1)
ts.plot(ts.USD, col = 'blue', xlab = "Year", ylab = "TL Value",main="USD")

Analysis

Fluctiation in exchange rates affects economics statistics.USD and Euro show similar changes. Both of them show similar changes witch CPI,Cumhuriyet gold price and Loan. But, they don’t show similar export and import. This doesn’t mean that exchange rates don’t affect import and export. However, other parameters affect exports and imports more than exchange rates.Import and export show similar changes but considering last years, When import decreasing, export doesn’t decrease.Because, Turkish lira depreciation makes import difficult.
